<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-28T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-28T17:00:00-05:00" n="142" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d142">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.5017/12–2844: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Donnelly</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-28T19:00:00-03:00">December
                                    28, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 9:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4551. Department’s circular, December 21, 10 p.m.; my 4534, December 26,
                            8 p.m. Souza Costa said to me today “You must help me out of the coffee
                            crisis”. I told him again that our Government will not increase coffee
                            price ceilings to which he remarked “Then I will probably go to
                            Washington to discuss the matter with officials there”.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Donnelly</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>